<h3>Brief CV</h3>
<p>I presently am <i>charg&eacute; de recherche</i> (CRCN) at CNRS, and have held this position since October 2008.</p>
<p>In November 2017, I obtained my <a href="papers/Habilitation.pdf"><i>habilitation &agrave; diriger des recherches</i></a>.</p>
<p>In 2007-2008, I was one of the very first recipients of the <a href="https://www.sciencesmaths-paris.fr/en/">Fondation Sciences Math&eacute;matiques de Paris</a> post-doctoral fellowships, under which I worked at the laboratory <i>Preuves, Programmes et Syst&egrave;mes</i> (now <a href="https://www.irif.fr/en/index">Institut de Recherche en Informatique Fondamentale</a>), <a href="http://www.univ-paris-diderot.fr/">Universit&eacute; Paris 7</a>.</p>
<p>Before that, in 2006-2007 I was post-doctoral fellow at LIPN&ndash;<a href="http://www.univ-paris13.fr">Universit&eacute; Paris 13</a>. My fellowship was supported by the <a href="http://www.agence-nationale-recherche.fr/">ANR</a> project "NOCoST".</p>
<p>Prior to that, in the period 2003-2006, I had an <i>allocation de recherche</i> (Ph.D. grant) to develop my <a href="papers/Thesis.pdf">Ph.D. thesis</a> at the <i>Institut de Math&eacute;matiques de Luminy</i> (now <a href="http://www.i2m.univ-amu.fr">Institut de Math&eacute;matiques de Marseille</a>), Universit&eacute; Aix-Marseille 2 (now <a href="http://www.univ-amu.fr/">Aix Marseille Universit&eacute;</a>), under the supervision of <a href="https://www.i2m.univ-amu.fr/perso/laurent.regnier/">Laurent Regnier</a>, which I defended in December 2006. The thesis was developed jointly with the Department of Philosophy of the <a href="http://www.uniroma3.it">Universit&agrave; Roma Tre</a>, with <a href="http://www.matfis.uniroma3.it/persone/docenti/docenti_beige.php?persona=71">V. Michele Abrusci</a> as co-supervisor. During my stay in Marseille, I was also <i>moniteur</i> (Teaching Assistant) at the Departments of Mathematics and of Computer Science in Luminy.</p>
<p>Before starting my Ph.D. thesis, in 2002-2003, I studied at Universit&eacute; Aix-Marseille 2 to obtain a DEA (<i>Dipl&ocirc;me d'&Eacute;tudes Approfondies</i>, or M.S.) in Discrete Mathematics and Theoretical Computer Science.</p>
<p>Prior to that, that is, before 2002, I studied <a href="https://www.inf.uniroma3.it/?lang=en">Computer Engineering in Rome</a>, spoke not even a word of French, and had no idea whatsoever I was going to end up living in France.</p>
<!--p>A more complete CV may be found <a href="CV-fr.pdf">here</a> (in French, sorry).</p-->
